cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with data transport and communication in IoT settings. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper focuses on the use of UAVs for data collection and delivery. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a heuristic solution to the optimisation problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the management of a team of UAVs for data muling. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the coordination of ground sensors and UAVs for efficient data transport.
